HEy there;
I've found a bug, dunno if it's PHP or PHP GTK but when I brought it up on the IRC channel last night I was asked to post here.
This line of code will cause PHP to seg fault when run:
$tilesPix[0]=gdk::pixmap_create_from_xpm_d($tilewindow->$window,null,$blankTile32by32xpm);
The PHP parser SHOULD pick up an error -- namely, it *SHOULD* be $tilewindow->window INSTEAD of $tilewindow->$window -- but instead of giving a parse error, PHP seg faults. This line of code works 100% as:
$tilesPix[0]=gdk::pixmap_create_from_xpm_d($tilewindow->window,null,$blankTile32by32xpm);
