I am trying to extend the GtkMenuBar object so that I can add an array of 
values to a menu.

For example.

======  CLASS CODE ======

<?php
class GtkMenuBarExt extends GtkMenuBar{
     function fill_from_array($items){
         if (!is_array($items)){
         return false;
         }

         foreach ($items as $menu_name => $menu_array){
         $menu =& new GtkMenu();
             foreach ($menu_array as $item_name => $item_label){
             $item =& new GtkMenuItem($item_label);
             $item->show();
             $menu->append($item);
             }
         $menu->show();
         parent::add($menu);
         }
     }
}
?>


====== MAIN SCRIPT ========

$menubar =& new GtkMenuBarExt();
$menu_items = Array("file" => Array("new" => "New", "save" => "Save"), 
"help" => Array("help_contents" => "Help", "about" => "About..."));
$menubar->fill_from_array($menu_items);
$menubar->show();

//// pack this into the window etc

==========================

I have tried everything, but the menu doesn't seem to have the array items 
added.  Am I losing a reference somewhere, or is this something php-gtk 
can't do?

